### Cache demo — LogisticsService.Carriers is deliberately slow.
### Set LOGISTICS_CARRIERS_DELAY_MS in the env to tune the sleep
### (default 2000 ms). The consumption view caches the response:
###
###   @federation.delegate: { cache: { ttl: 300000 } }
###   entity Carriers as projection on logistics.Carriers;
###
### First request: ~2 s (cache miss → hits the slow provider).
### Subsequent requests: a few ms (cache hit) until the TTL expires.
###
### Open the browser dev tools or use VS Code REST Client and compare
### request timings between the first and second call.

### 1) Cold — watch this one: it will take ~2 seconds
GET http://localhost:4005/odata/v4/sales-intel/Carriers

### 2) Warm — same request, served from cache in ms
GET http://localhost:4005/odata/v4/sales-intel/Carriers

### 3) Different $filter → different cache entry → cold again
GET http://localhost:4005/odata/v4/sales-intel/Carriers?$filter=serviceLevel eq 'express'

### 4) Flush the cache for the whole service
POST http://localhost:4005/pipeline/flush
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"Carriers"}

### 5) After flush — cold again
GET http://localhost:4005/odata/v4/sales-intel/Carriers
